This hot and bitter drink comes with a slice of lemon the rim. When drunk, it has a hint of spice, milk, and...mint? This will surely get your senses buzzing, though your taste buds may question it.

This seems to be a cheap, light beer that's only notable quality is the ease at which it goes down. This makes it popular for sailors and soldiers looking to get drunk quickly and cheaply. The beer isn't terrible, strictly speaking, but it's greenish hue can be somewhat off-putting. Its hang-overs, however, are positivity brutal.

This blend of citrus juices is mixed and sweetened to just the right taste.
A fine bubbly concoction, this champagne is suitable for any grand event, but is usually reserved for weddings.

Created by the Gnome Giggledunk Gnafflepot to make sure that drinks can be both drinkable and eatable. As you shake the bottle containing the liquid, the liquid will start transforming into a Jelly of sorts, which you easily can poor from the bottle and, later on, eat with a spoon. This transformation neutralizes the alcohol and creates a sugary and sweet Jelly, enjoyed greatly by many. 
The drinkable part is sweet, with a hint of sugar. It can be served on almost any occasion and it is most enjoyable ice-cold.

Created by the Gnome Giggledunk Gnafflepot to make sure that drinks can be both drinkable and eatable. As you shake the bottle containing the liquid, the liquid will start transforming into a Jelly of sorts, which you easily can poor from the bottle and, later on, eat with a spoon. This transformation magically neutralizes the alcohol and creates a bitter and thick Jelly, also eatable with a spoon. This drink is favored by many, mostly Hins and the ones with Orc blood running through their veins. 
The drinkable part is like the Jelly, bitter, swampy but also quite strong.
